[Name] Karmen
[Summary] A window manager designed to "just work"
[Description] Karmen is an easy-to-use window manager for X, written by Johan Veenhuizen. It is designed to ?just work?. There is no configuration file and no library dependencies other than Xlib. The input focus model is click-to-focus. Karmen aims at ICCCM and EWMH compliance.
[License] MIT-like
[Homepage] https://karmen.sourceforge.net/
